<item>
  <title>Ben Black</title>
  <link>https://DaMIfLL.github.io/current/Ben.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<section id="about-ben" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="about-ben">About Ben</h2>
<p>Sarah joined our company in 2018 and has been instrumental in modernizing our technology stack. She holds a Master’s degree in Computer Science from MIT and is a frequent speaker at tech conferences.</p>
<section id="achievements" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="achievements">Achievements</h3>
<ul>
<li>Led the migration of our monolithic application to microservices</li>
<li>Reduced infrastructure costs by 40% through cloud optimization</li>
<li>Grew the engineering team from 5 to 50 people</li>
<li>Published research on distributed systems in leading journals</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="education" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="education">Education</h3>
<ul>
<li>M.S. Computer Science, MIT, 2007</li>
<li>B.S. Computer Engineering, Stanford University, 2005</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="contact" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="contact">Contact</h3>
<ul>
<li>Email: sarah.johnson@company.com</li>
<li>LinkedIn: <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/sarahjohnson">linkedin.com/in/sarahjohnson</a></li>
<li>Twitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/sarahj_tech"><span class="citation" data-cites="sarahj_tech">@sarahj_tech</span></a></li>
</ul>


</section>
</section>

 ]]></description>
